# The metamodel-gen tool (and its golden-file tests) write their Markdown outputs with
# LF newlines. Without these rules, core.autocrlf=true makes Git expect CRLF in the
# working tree and flags every generated file as "modified" after each generation run,
# even though the content is identical. Pin the generated artifacts to LF so Git and the
# generator agree and the spurious diffs stop.
knowledge/** text eol=lf
tools/metamodel-gen/Hypha.MetamodelGen.Tests/Expected/** text eol=lf

# Handlebars templates are read verbatim and their newlines flow into generated output;
# keep them LF so generation is deterministic regardless of platform checkout settings.
*.hbs text eol=lf
